It's finally done, Shura's MotoAdventures is live. It sure was a wild ride, what started out as a small test as "can it be done?" then turned into "okay it can be done, but is it fun?". I don't have an answer for that but I at least tried. 
When I made Eru's game, it was always meant to be just a silly minigame inspired by her tweet. Something that would make you go "that's so funny she's twerking like in her tweet" and I was very happy with how that turned out. With this project, though, I really tried to make a proper game and I even went so far as to make a level editor for it and all that shit. However I'm not entirely convinced about the end result. The rear wheel is too bouncy, the bike is a little too chaotic and difficult to maneuver. Is it fun? Who knows. I made some levels that are a little bit on the hard side, probably would take like 15~30 minutes to beat the entire thing.
Some anon mentioned that I should release the level editor, well it's right there in the game. You can make a level and then click on "Save" and it will export that json with the level data. If you have the patience to make a level and you want me to include it just post the json here (or in a pastebin or something) and I will add it. You can specify a level name and author name if you want.
I will try to do better next time. I have several ideas in mind which might or might not come to life.
